{
  "text": "The fixed cells were permeabilized with 0.1% Triton-PBS for 5 min and washed thrice with PBS for 10 min. After blocking with 1% bovine serum album for 1 h, cells were stained with FITC-labeled phalloidin for 40 min and then with DAPI for 5 min at 37°C in the dark, followed by washing thrice again. Finally, F-actin ring formation was observed with a fluorescence microscope (Leica Microsystems, Wetzlar, Germany). [CITATION_1] ",
